================================================================================
          YARN & MAPREDUCE STEPWISE CORE COMPONENTS (SHORTEST PRODUCTION FLOW)
================================================================================

【RESOURCE MANAGER (RM)】 == Master daemon
- Master daemon managing cluster-wide resources

【SCHEDULER (under RM)】
- Allocate containers

【APPLICATION MANAGER (under RM)】
- Accept job submission and create FIRST container for ApplicationMaster

【APPLICATION MASTER (AM)】
- Runs INSIDE AM Container (1 GB RAM, 1 core typical)
- Negotiate with Scheduler

【NODE MANAGER (NM)】
- Launch containers on assigned node and monitor their resource usage
- Send heartbeat

【CONTAINER】
- Isolated fraction of physical resources (RAM + CPU) allocated on a node where actual tasks (Mapper/Reducer) run

【COMBINER】 == (Runs right after Mapper)
- Runs locally inside the Mapper container as a mini-reducer
- Reduces network overhead by aggregating data before it leaves the local node
- Required to prevent network bottlenecks during heavy data processing

【SHUFFLE & SORT】 == (Runs between Mapper and Reducer)
- Transfers intermediate key-value data across the network from Mappers to Reducers
- Sorts and groups data by key so that each Reducer gets a clean, unified set of inputs
- Required because Reducers cannot aggregate data until all identical keys are in one place

【REPLICATION】 == (Runs during Final Output Save)
- Duplicates final output blocks across multiple physical machines (default factor = 3)
- Places copies across different racks using Rack Awareness Policy
- Required for high availability and fault tolerance so data is never lost if a node crashes

